The paper focuses on deep learning for image retrieval, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel loss function for similarity-preserving learning, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also evaluates its method on three datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR), multimedia (cs.MM), or computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories.
